def: Vomiting flames, as a volcano. W. Thompson. (1745).
A seed vessel resembling a silique, but about as broad as it islong. See Silique.
Hanging; suspended; pendent; pendulous. Bacon.The long, pensile branches of the birches. W. Howitt.

Nearsightedness; shortsightedness; a condition of the eye inwhich the rays from distant object are brought to a focus before theyreach the retina, and hence form an indistinct image; while the raysfrom very near objects are normally converged so as to produce adistinct image. It is corrected by the use of a concave lens.
An Australian tree (Casuarina), and its red wood, used forcabinetwork; also, the trees Stenocarpus salignus of New South Wales,and Banksia compar of Queensland.
Having the shape of a gourd seed; -- said of certain smallworms.
A compound cordial, in the form of a confection, deriving itsname from the kermes insect, its principal ingredient.
